post_text: The first day of in-person and distance learning is in the books at Adams and those of us in the front office are happy to see all of our hard work come to fruition today! It was so great to see the (masked but smiling) faces of our students on campus, as well as the bright and shining faces of our remote learning students on screen! We are thankful for each and every one of you!

A great time was had by all at the All Fore! the Kids Golf Tournament this weekend, which benefitted Adams Traditional Academy. It was fun to see quite a few teachers who had been sponsored to play out on the links! The weather was beautiful and, amazingly, every shot landed in the middle of the fairway...

A very big thank you goes out to the tournament sponsors: Industrial Storage (the Woolery Family), Farmers Insurance (the Gould Family), Healthy Kin (the Brown Family) and Rival (the Van Wagner Family). Thank you for your generous support.

We greatly appreciate the parents, volunteers and administration who made this event a big success and are making a difference for ATA!

post_text: This is a reminder that our November PIN meeting is scheduled for Wednesday, November 14th at 6:00 p.m. in Building B, MPR. Please note that in order to provide all parents with an opportunity to discuss items, only announced topics will be discussed at this PIN meeting. If you have a topic you would like to discuss at the next PIN meeting, please email the PIN chair at lisamccauley@cox.net.
